<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Earning your keep</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Radyen the Honorable">Radyen the Honorable</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 4:21 a.m. 7/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Earning your keep<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>I have one complaint to air. I have seen several lower level characters walking around in full chain mail. Albeit that I am happy for their success, I can not believe that so many level 10 players have earned that kind of money. I have been witness to a few players even coming right out and asking other players for donations. Most of us have worked long and hard at abtaining our armor and weapons, why should some not have to? The one solution that i purpose is this, don't give people money. I understand that you think that you are helping out your friends, or doing a good deed, but what type of gaming experience will you get if everything is handed to you. It soils that fact that some people have worked extremely hard to obtain their belongings. I realize that by pointing out this that nothing will change but I just want it on the record.

</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
<br><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0><BR><A NAME="PostResponse"><p><font face=arial size=2><font size=3><b>Post a Response</b></A></font>
